  "summary": "Probes AWS ECS task credentials endpoint and beacons to webhook.site on require",
  "details": "On require('cryptoco-auth'), index.js performs an HTTP GET to 169.254.170.2 (the AWS ECS task IAM credentials metadata endpoint) at a hardcoded credential path, then POSTs the response to a hardcoded webhook.site bin (https://webhook.site/50a891aa-a14a-4ccb-8d96-62542945b9fc). The package exports no functionality, ships no README, and consists only of this 26-line probe — its sole effect when imported in an AWS ECS environment is to attempt cloud credential reconnaissance and report results to an attacker-controlled endpoint. The name 'cryptoco-auth' suggests a typosquat / dependency-confusion lure for an auth library that does not exist.",
